.TH NETCTL 1 "2025" "netctl" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
netctl \- async network management tool with NetworkManager compatibility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B netctl
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B netctl
is an async network management tool built on tokio for high performance.
It provides interface management, WiFi support, access point mode, DHCP server configuration,
DNS management, routing control, and NetworkManager D-Bus compatibility.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Device Management
.TP
.B device list
List all network devices
.SS Interface Management
.TP
.B interface list
List all network interfaces
.TP
.B interface show \fIINTERFACE\fR
Show detailed information about an interface
.TP
.B interface up \fIINTERFACE\fR
Bring an interface up
.TP
.B interface down \fIINTERFACE\fR
Bring an interface down
.TP
.B interface set-ip \fIINTERFACE\fR \fIADDRESS\fR --prefix \fIPREFIX\fR
Set IP address on an interface
.TP
.B interface del-ip \fIINTERFACE\fR \fIADDRESS\fR --prefix \fIPREFIX\fR
Delete IP address from an interface
.TP
.B interface set-mac \fIINTERFACE\fR \fIMAC\fR
Set MAC address on an interface
.TP
.B interface set-mtu \fIINTERFACE\fR \fIMTU\fR
Set MTU on an interface
.SS WiFi Operations
.TP
.B wifi list
List all WiFi interfaces
.TP
.B wifi scan \fIINTERFACE\fR
Scan for WiFi networks
.TP
.B wifi info \fIINTERFACE\fR
Show WiFi device information
.TP
.B wifi get-reg
Get regulatory domain
.TP
.B wifi set-reg \fICOUNTRY\fR
Set regulatory domain (e.g., US, GB, JP)
.TP
.B wifi get-txpower \fIINTERFACE\fR
Get TX power
.TP
.B wifi set-txpower \fIINTERFACE\fR \fIPOWER\fR
Set TX power (e.g., 20dBm)
.SS Access Point
.TP
.B ap start \fIINTERFACE\fR --ssid \fISSID\fR [--password \fIPASSWORD\fR] [--channel \fICHANNEL\fR] [--band \fIBAND\fR]
Start access point mode
.TP
.B ap stop
Stop access point
.TP
.B ap status
Show access point status
.SS DHCP Server
.TP
.B dhcp start \fIINTERFACE\fR --range-start \fIIP\fR --range-end \fIIP\fR --gateway \fIIP\fR --dns \fIIP\fR
Start DHCP server with dora
.TP
.B dhcp write-config \fIINTERFACE\fR --range-start \fIIP\fR --range-end \fIIP\fR --gateway \fIIP\fR --dns \fIIP\fR
Write DHCP configuration file
.SS Routing
.TP
.B route add-default \fIGATEWAY\fR [--interface \fIINTERFACE\fR]
Add default route
.SS Connection Management
.TP
.B connection list
List saved connections
.TP
.B connection up \fINAME\fR
Activate a connection
.TP
.B connection down \fINAME\fR
Deactivate a connection
.TP
.B connection delete \fINAME\fR
Delete a connection
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Print help information
.TP
.B -V, --version
Print version information
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/netctl/
Configuration directory
.TP
.I /etc/netctl/*.nctl
Connection configuration files
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/netctl/examples/
Example configuration files
.TP
.I /run/netctl/
Runtime state directory
.TP
.I /run/netctl/hostapd.conf
Generated hostapd configuration
.TP
.I /run/netctl/dora.yaml
Generated dora DHCP configuration
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List all network interfaces:
.EX
netctl interface list
.EE
.TP
Scan for WiFi networks:
.EX
netctl wifi scan wlan0
.EE
.TP
Start an access point:
.EX
netctl ap start wlan0 --ssid "MyAP" --password "secret123" --channel 6
.EE
.TP
Configure DHCP server:
.EX
netctl dhcp start wlan0 --range-start 10.255.24.10 \\
    --range-end 10.255.24.250 --gateway 10.255.24.1 --dns 10.255.24.1
.EE
.TP
Set IP address:
.EX
netctl interface set-ip eth0 192.168.1.100 --prefix 24
.EE
.TP
Set regulatory domain:
.EX
netctl wifi set-reg US
.EE
